  "issue_title": "bug: LLM stream producer not cancelled on client disconnect",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\n`handle_chat_stream` in `crates/genie-core/src/server.rs` joins the LLM producer and SSE consumer with `tokio::join!`. When a client disconnects mid-stream, the consumer exits immediately but `tokio::join!` does not cancel the producer \u2014 the full LLM inference runs to completion, burning CPU/GPU and credits for a response nobody receives.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start `genie-core` with any chat-capable model loaded.\n2. Send a `/api/chat` streaming request that will produce a long response (e.g. `\"write me a 500-word essay\"`).\n3. Cancel the HTTP request (browser refresh, `curl` interrupt, closed tab) within the first few tokens.\n4. Watch `journalctl -u genie-core` \u2014 the LLM continues to log token generation and the API call completes in full despite the client being gone.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLLM inference is interrupted as soon as the write side detects the disconnect; no further tokens are generated or billed.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nFull inference runs to completion. The producer's callback keeps calling `tx.send(token)`, gets `Err(SendError)` on every call once `rx` is dropped, and silently swallows each error via `let _ = ...`. There is no `select!`, `abort`, `CancellationToken`, or timeout in the file.\n\n```\n$ grep -n 'select!\\|abort\\|CancellationToken\\|timeout' crates/genie-core/src/server.rs\n(no output)\n```\n\n### Hardware\n\nJetson Orin Nano Super 8 GB\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n6.x\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n1.0.0-alpha.9\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n`crates/genie-core/src/server.rs:566\u2013614`\n\n\nlet (tx, mut rx) = tokio::sync::mpsc::unbounded_channel::<String>();\nlet producer = llm.chat_stream(&messages, Some(512), move |token| {\n    let _ = tx.send(token.to_string());  // error silently discarded\n});\n\n// ...consumer defined here...\n\nlet (llm_result, state_result) = tokio::join!(producer, consumer);\n\n\n`tokio::join!` waits for **both** futures regardless of which one finishes first.\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n## Fix Sketch\n\nReplace `tokio::join!` with `tokio::select!` so the producer is dropped (and cancelled at its next `.await`) as soon as the consumer exits:\n\n```rust\nlet state_result = tokio::select! {\n    r = consumer => r,\n    _ = producer => Err(anyhow::anyhow!(\"producer finished before consumer\")),\n};\n```\n\nAlternatively, thread a `tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken` through the producer callback for explicit cooperative cancellation \u2014 useful if `chat_stream` is not cancel-safe.\n\n## Environment\n\n- **File:** `crates/genie-core/src/server.rs`, line 614\n- **Git SHA:** `5920e31` (tip of `perf/25-core-isolation-voice-latency`)\n- **Confirmed by:** static code inspection; not hardware-specific\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-22T15:38:27.000Z",
